Health workers were being recognised for the work they've done during the COVID-19 pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - It has been a year since the first case of COVID-19 was reported in South Africa. Health workers were being recognised for the work they've done during the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Professor Karim reflects on the past year Health Minister Zweli Mkhize attended the ceremony at Entabeni Hospital.  